      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "In commit \"wallet: Replace CDataStream& with Span<char> where possible\" (fafeffc6b23bea9addc091f69fe72440af185db8)\r\n\r\nMight be worth mentioning in a comment here that memory_cleanse will be called on all these spans. I didn't realize this was happening, even after your previous comment in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19292#discussion_r442239967. You could imagine this leading to bugs if for example an EraseKey call was made after a ReadKey call with the same span, nothing would be erased because the key would be wiped between calls.",
